enumMember.name: UNKNOWN
enumMember.description: Control path availability from Baseband to GNSS receiver unknown.

enumMember.name: CONTROL_PATH_EXIST
enumMember.description: Control path exists from Baseband to GNSS receiver. Baseband can configure GNSS receiver.

enumMember.name: NO_CONTROL_PATH
enumMember.description: No control path from Baseband to GNSS receiver. Baseband cannot configure GNSS receiver. Error in cable, connectors or caused by intermediate HW.

enumMember.name: UNSUPPORTED
enumMember.description: GNSS receiver does not support control from Baseband. Applies to GPS01.

enumMember.name: UNKNOWN
enumMember.description: Displayed at start-up phase and when there is no GNSS receiver connected.

enumMember.name: UPGRADE_UNSUPPORTED
enumMember.description: Connected GNSS receiver does not support firmware upgrade.

enumMember.name: NO_CONTROL
enumMember.description: Node is not in control of GNSS receiver.

enumMember.name: DOWNLOAD_ONGOING
enumMember.description: Downloading of firmware to GNSS receiver is ongoing.

enumMember.name: EVALUATING_RESTART_PRECONDITIONS
enumMember.description: Latest firmware is downloaded to GNSS receiver. Before ordering GNSS receiver to restart with latest firmware, but node is evaluating sky visibility to find a time window where GNSS receiver can lock to satellites.

enumMember.name: SKY_VISIBILITY_LIMITED
enumMember.description: Latest firmware downloaded. Node will not order GNSS receiver to restart on latest firmware due to too limited sky visibility.

enumMember.name: RESTART_ORDERED
enumMember.description: GNSS receiver ordered to restart with latest firmware.

enumMember.name: OK
enumMember.description: GNSS receiver use latest firmware.

enumMember.name: FIRMWARE_REJECTED
enumMember.description: GNSS receiver rejects firmware in UP.

enumMember.name: FILE_TRANSFER_REJECTED
enumMember.description: GNSS receiver rejected file transfer.

enumMember.name: DOWNLOAD_FAILED
enumMember.description: Download of firmware to GNSS receiver has failed, but it was not rejected.

enumMember.name: FIRMWARE_MISMATCH
enumMember.description: GNSS receiver is running older firmware than firmware in UP. GNSS receiver failed to start on firmware downloaded from UP, or user have by action ordered GNSS receiver to start from slot which does not contain latest firmware.

enumMember.name: UNKNOWN
enumMember.description: Observation point mode is not known.

enumMember.name: SURVEY
enumMember.description: GNSS receiver is in survey mode, time and position are continuously calculated.

enumMember.name: POSITION_HOLD
enumMember.description: GNSS receiver locked to fixed position, which is used to calculate time.

enumMember.name: RELEASE_CONTROL
enumMember.description: Get control of GNSS receiver.

enumMember.name: GET_CONTROL
enumMember.description: Release control of GNSS receiver.

enumMember.name: ENABLE
enumMember.description: Enable automatic resurvey.

enumMember.name: DISABLE
enumMember.description: Disable automatic resurvey.

enumMember.name: EXECUTE
enumMember.description: Initiate manual resurvey.

enumMember.name: CANCEL
enumMember.description: Cancel manual resurvey in progress.

enumMember.name: STATUS
enumMember.description: Display resurvey status and position information.

enumMember.name: HW_FAULT
enumMember.description: Hardware fault reported from the receiver.

enumMember.name: OK
enumMember.description: Indicates fully operational GNSS receiver.

enumMember.name: NO_TIME
enumMember.description: No time reported.

enumMember.name: NO_MESSAGES
enumMember.description: No messages received.

enumMember.name: PROTOCOL_NOT_RECOGNIZED
enumMember.description: The protocol used by the receiver is not recognised.

enumMember.name: LOSS_OF_1PPS_SIGNAL
enumMember.description: 1PPS synchronization signal lost.

enumMember.name: SYNCHRONIZED
enumMember.description: GNSS receiver is synchronized to satellites.

enumMember.name: NOT_SYNCHRONIZED
enumMember.description: GNSS receiver is not synchronized to satellites.

enumMember.name: UNKNOWN
enumMember.description: No contact with GNSS receiver.

enumMember.name: WANTED_GNSS_USED
enumMember.description: Wanted satellite system used by GNSS receiver.

enumMember.name: DISABLED_LICENSE
enumMember.description: Wanted satellite system not used by GNSS receiver. Missing or deactivated Multiple GNSS Support license.

enumMember.name: GNSS_REC_UNREACHABLE
enumMember.description: Wanted satellite system not used by GNSS receiver. Control path to GNSS receiver missing.

enumMember.name: WANTED_GNSS_UNSUPPORTED
enumMember.description: Connected GNSS receiver does not support wanted satellite system. GPS03 receiver needed.

enumMember.name: GNSS_REC_CONFIG_FAULT
enumMember.description:

Another node sharing GNSS receiver has configured it differently. Attribute multipleGnssWanted needs to be changed on one of nodes to get matching configuration.

enumMember.name: BDS
enumMember.description: BeiDou Navigation Satellite System.

class.name: GnssInfo

action.name: gnssReceiverResurvey
action.description: Enable or disable automatic self-resurvey, or perform manual self-resurvey on connected GNSS receiver.

parameter.name: noOfSatellites
parameter.description:
noOfSatellites can be in range 4..24, and is used only when action is set to execute.
If action is executed successfully, result is empty string. If action failed, result is string with explanation.

action.name: gnssReceiverReset
action.description: Initiate reset of connected GNSS receiver.

parameter.name: action
parameter.description: Set action to execute to initiate reset.

parameter.name: slotNumber
parameter.description: GRU firmware slot number is used to restart GRU on particular firmware revision.

action.statusInformation: Since 19.Q1. Planned to be removed. Replaced by gnssReceiverRestart.

action.name: getGnssReceiverControl
action.description: Give node control of GNSS receiver.

parameter.name: action
parameter.description:
Set action to get or release control of GNSS receiver.
If action is executed successfully, result is empty string. If action failed, result is string with explanation.
Action fails in following cases: - Executed on node with connected GNSS receiver of older generation than GRU04. - GRU04 is connected to node, but node has no control over GRU04.

action.name: gnssReceiverRestart
action.description:
Initiate restart of connected GNSS receiver.
Action can be executed if GPS02, GPS03 or GRU04 receiver is connected to node.

parameter.name: action
parameter.description:
Set action to initiate reset.
If action is executed successfully, result is empty string. If action failed, result is string with explanation.
Action fails if executed on node which has: - GPS01 connected. - GPS02, GPS03 or GRU04 connected, but there is no control path towards GNSS receiver. - GRU04 connected, but there is no control over GNSS receiver.

action.name: gnssReceiverRestartFromSlot
action.description:
Initiate reset to different firmware slot on GRU04.
Action can be executed only if GRU04 receiver is connected to node.

parameter.name: slotNumber
parameter.description: GNSS receiver firmware slot number is used to restart GNSS receiver on particular firmware revision.

parameter.name: rollbackSlot
parameter.description:
If restart fails due to new defined slot number, GRU04 will autonomously restart to slot defined with rollbackSlot parameter.
If action is executed successfully, result is empty string. If action failed, result is string with explanation.
Action fails in following cases: - Executed on node with connected GNSS receiver of older generation than GRU04. - GRU04 is connected to node, but node has no control over GRU04.

attribute.description:
Altitude of GNSS receiver antenna.
In survey mode, instantaneous calculated altitude of antenna. In position-hold mode, altitude of antenna averaged over survey period.

attribute.name: hdop

attribute.name: multipleGnssStatus
attribute.description:
Multiple GNSS usage status.
If wanted satellite system is used by GNSS receiver, or if there is mismatch between actual and wanted satellite system usage including possible mismatch cause.

attribute.name: multipleGnssWanted
attribute.description:
Wanted satellite system to be used by GNSS receiver.
GNSS receiver GPS03 starts by using GPS and GLONASS. It can be configured to use different satellite systems. Earlier GNSS receiver products support only GPS.
Dependencies: UNKNOWN is not applicable for wanted satellite system.
